The 2019 MyBroadband Conference and Expo takes place on 17 October, hosting South Africa’s top ICT companies and 3,000 ICT executives and decision-makers. The conference will take place at the Gallagher Convention Centre and will feature excellent exhibitions from the country’s biggest IT and telecoms companies. Executives from MTN, Liquid Telecom, Vodacom, and SqwidNet will also speak at the conference, providing insight into their companies and the latest trends in the industry. Their presentations will be delivered to the 3,000 delegates in attendance and streamed live by MyBroadband. The MyBroadband Conference is made possible thanks to sponsorships from the country’s top ICT companies. MTN is the lead sponsor of the 2019 event, while Liquid Telecom is the official event partner. Other prominent sponsors include Vodacom, WIOCC, SqwidNet, Miro, Nology, Scoop, Nashua, TOA Cable, CBI Electric, Codehesion, Cipherwave, and Home-Connect. These sponsors will showcase their products and services at the conference, and are able to interact with the 3,000 delegates and other industry players. The 2019 conference is therefore the perfect meeting place for any company or individual in the ICT space. To find out how you can be a part of the conference, contact: Please note that many sponsorship opportunities are already sold out. For more information on the 2019 MyBroadband Conference, visit the conference website. The video below provides an overview of what companies and delegates can expect at the MyBroadband Conference. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>